junctions. The lack of such a private right of action can render a rule less enforceable in practice.\n\nTheoretical frameworks like Hart's concept of law (primary rules of obligation backed by secondary rules of recognition, change, and adjudication) inform this analysis. A purely aspirational rule lacks these secondary rules. The challenge in AI governance is translating high-level principles (e.g., transparency, accountability) into enforceable, context-specific requirements through harmonized standards, conformity assessments, and clear liability regimes, as attempted in the EU's product liability framework adapted for AI.",
